WEBVTT

00:00.134 --> 00:02.835
¶¶

00:09.543 --> 00:12.511
<i> ¶ I was a girl in the village</i>
<i> doing all right ¶</i>

00:12.513 --> 00:14.880
<i> ¶ Then I became</i>
<i> a princess overnight ¶</i>

00:14.882 --> 00:17.616
<i> ¶ Now I gotta figure out</i>
<i> how to do it right ¶</i>

00:17.618 --> 00:19.885
<i> ¶ So much to learn</i>
<i> and see ¶</i>

00:19.887 --> 00:22.554
<i> ¶ Up in the castle</i>
<i> with my new family ¶</i>

00:22.556 --> 00:25.290
<i> ¶ In a school</i>
<i> that's just for royalty ¶</i>

00:25.292 --> 00:29.495
<i> ¶ A whole enchanted world</i>
<i> is waiting for me ¶</i>

00:29.497 --> 00:33.565
<i> -¶ I'm so excited to be ¶</i>
<i> -¶ Sofia the First ¶</i>

00:36.670 --> 00:37.903
<i>¶ Sofia the First ¶</i>

00:37.905 --> 00:39.671
<i> ¶ Making my way ¶</i>

00:39.673 --> 00:42.841
<i> -¶ It's an adventure</i>
<i> every day ¶</i>
<i> -¶ Sofia ¶</i>

00:42.843 --> 00:45.477
<i> -¶ It's gonna be my time ¶</i>
<i> -¶ Sofia ¶</i>

00:45.479 --> 00:51.550
<i> ¶ To show them all</i>
<i> that I'm Sofia the First ¶</i>

00:58.893 --> 01:01.493
[Sofia reads]

01:01.495 --> 01:05.330
[Baileywick]
We need more flowers
for the flower sculptures!

01:05.332 --> 01:08.367
More chocolate
for the chocolate waterfall!

01:08.369 --> 01:10.335
[Amber] Oh, I love weddings!

01:10.337 --> 01:11.437
I don't.

01:11.439 --> 01:13.172
Having to greet
all those people?

01:13.174 --> 01:14.740
How am I supposed to remember

01:14.742 --> 01:16.442
everyone's name
and where they're from?

01:16.444 --> 01:18.610
Don't worry, James,
you're going to do great!

01:18.612 --> 01:19.945
I'll help you practice.

01:19.947 --> 01:23.749
Okay, How will you greet
the king of the Kobolds?

01:23.751 --> 01:27.619
Uh, I'll-- I'll bow
and move my arms like
they're ocean waves!

01:27.621 --> 01:30.789
No, James, that's how you greet
the queen of the mermaids.

01:30.791 --> 01:33.792
You greet Kobalds
with their traditional
foot stomp, remember?

01:33.794 --> 01:37.896
Oh! Whatever you do,
don't touch their hair.

01:37.898 --> 01:39.698
Kobalds really
don't like that.

01:39.700 --> 01:41.600
Why did Aunt Tilly
have to invite

01:41.602 --> 01:43.969
so many different creatures
to her wedding, anyway?

01:43.971 --> 01:45.804
Uh, because she's
Aunt Tilly?

01:45.806 --> 01:47.973
And why is it my job
to greet them?

01:47.975 --> 01:50.943
Because, James, you're going
to be king one day,

01:50.945 --> 01:53.645
and that's one of your duties
as heir to the throne.

01:53.647 --> 01:55.914
Oh, right.
Well, I guess doing

01:55.916 --> 01:58.650
all this boring stuff will be
worth it once I'm king.

01:58.652 --> 02:01.220
Come on, James, it's
Aunt Tilly's wedding.

02:01.222 --> 02:02.821
It's going to be fun.

02:02.823 --> 02:05.057
¶ Incoming! ¶

02:05.059 --> 02:06.992
Aunt Tilly, do you
have wings?

02:06.994 --> 02:10.662
That's a very observant
observation you observed,

02:10.664 --> 02:12.731
and the answer is yes!

02:12.733 --> 02:15.834
But I can make them come
and go as I please.

02:15.836 --> 02:17.469
<i> Flutterous terminus!</i>

02:17.471 --> 02:18.904
<i> Flutterous featherus!</i>

02:18.906 --> 02:20.305
That's incredible!

02:20.307 --> 02:23.175
Isn't it?
This is a Whenever Wings wand,

02:23.177 --> 02:25.277
and I've been testing it out
all morning

02:25.279 --> 02:26.812
for a little surprise
I planned.

02:26.814 --> 02:28.847
<i> Flutterous terminus!</i>

02:28.849 --> 02:30.816
Sir Bartleby and I
want to make sure

02:30.818 --> 02:32.284
our wedding is memorable.

02:32.286 --> 02:33.652
I'm sure it will be!

02:33.654 --> 02:37.022
Your Majesties, it is time
for the royals to gather

02:37.024 --> 02:38.824
for the official
wedding portrait.

02:38.826 --> 02:40.492
Right this way,
please.

02:40.494 --> 02:42.594
Sofia, since you were the one

02:42.596 --> 02:44.796
who brought Sir Bartleby
and me together,

02:44.798 --> 02:47.833
I was hoping you would be
my maid of honor today.

02:47.835 --> 02:49.168
Of course, Aunt Tilly!

02:49.170 --> 02:51.436
I'd be, well, honored!

02:51.438 --> 02:54.806
Whiz-bang, here's your first
maid-of-honor assignment.

02:54.808 --> 02:57.843
Hold on to my Whenever Wings
wand until the ceremony,

02:57.845 --> 02:59.478
then when I give
you the signal,

02:59.480 --> 03:01.180
I'll need you to...
[whispers]

03:01.182 --> 03:03.615
Oh! That will be fun!

03:03.617 --> 03:07.152
Grand-queen, please stand
next to the bride,

03:07.154 --> 03:08.854
flanked by the king
and queen.

03:08.856 --> 03:11.690
Children, you're up front,

03:11.692 --> 03:13.592
heir to the throne
in the center.

03:15.129 --> 03:16.795
Oh, no, no, no, no.

03:16.797 --> 03:18.163
That's all wrong!

03:18.165 --> 03:20.732
Amber, you stand
in the middle.

03:20.734 --> 03:24.303
But, mother, the middle spot
is for the future king.

03:24.305 --> 03:26.538
No, I'm afraid not!

03:26.540 --> 03:28.707
You two need to switch.

03:28.709 --> 03:32.077
James is not next in line
to the throne,

03:32.079 --> 03:33.745
Amber is.

03:33.747 --> 03:34.746
I am?

03:34.748 --> 03:35.747
She is?

03:35.749 --> 03:37.049
Wait, what?

03:37.051 --> 03:38.884
I thought James
was going to be king.

03:38.886 --> 03:41.119
So did I.
So did everyone!

03:42.556 --> 03:43.922
Don't worry, children,

03:43.924 --> 03:45.824
we'll get this
all straightened out.

03:45.826 --> 03:47.893
Mother, I'm afraid
you are mistaken.

03:47.895 --> 03:51.029
The firstborn son
inherits the throne,

03:51.031 --> 03:52.764
like I did!

03:52.766 --> 03:56.868
Oh, but Roland, dear, that is
not how the law is written.

03:56.870 --> 04:00.872
Mum is right.
It's the firstborn child
who gets to rule.

04:00.874 --> 04:04.776
Indeed! Amber and James
may be twins,

04:04.778 --> 04:07.913
but Amber is
seven minutes older.

04:07.915 --> 04:10.082
Making her
the future queen!

04:12.753 --> 04:15.053
I just can't
believe any of this!

04:15.055 --> 04:17.956
Oh, then I'll show you.
Follow me!

04:17.958 --> 04:20.092
[giggling] Oh!

04:21.362 --> 04:23.161
Let me see.

04:24.732 --> 04:27.799
Here we are!
Heir to the throne.

04:27.801 --> 04:30.102
"Rulership of the kingdom

04:30.104 --> 04:31.970
shall be passed down

04:31.972 --> 04:34.573
from generation
to generation..."

04:34.575 --> 04:37.576
"From firstborn child
to firstborn child!"

04:37.578 --> 04:40.312
That-- that's me!
I was born first!

04:40.314 --> 04:42.381
Yeah, we know that.

04:42.383 --> 04:43.582
But how can this be?

04:43.584 --> 04:45.250
If that's the law,

04:45.252 --> 04:48.253
then Tilly would've been offered
the throne instead of me.

04:48.255 --> 04:50.589
Well, truth be told,
I was.

04:50.591 --> 04:52.658
-[all] You were?
-That's right.

04:52.660 --> 04:54.993
Many years ago,
I was offered the crown,

04:54.995 --> 04:56.895
but I
couldn't accept it.

04:56.897 --> 04:59.798
I knew I wanted
to be an adventurer,

04:59.800 --> 05:03.101
and that my baby brother
would make a much better king.

05:03.103 --> 05:06.071
But why didn't anyone
ever tell me?

05:06.073 --> 05:08.473
Because we knew
that being king

05:08.475 --> 05:10.409
was all
you ever wanted,

05:10.411 --> 05:12.311
and your father
and I knew

05:12.313 --> 05:15.414
that it was all
you could ever do.

05:15.416 --> 05:17.916
I guess that's true...

05:17.918 --> 05:20.118
And we knew you'd be
great at it.

05:20.120 --> 05:22.854
Maybe being king
is all<i> I</i> ever wanted!

05:22.856 --> 05:24.823
Did anyone ever think of that?

05:24.825 --> 05:28.160
I'm so very sorry, son,
but the law is the law.

05:28.162 --> 05:30.862
James, you don't even like
doing most of the things

05:30.864 --> 05:34.032
a king has to do--
you said it's boring!

05:34.034 --> 05:36.301
And you think you're
going to be a good queen?

05:36.303 --> 05:39.004
You've always been more worried
about how you look in your tiara

05:39.006 --> 05:41.306
than how the people
in the kingdom are doing!

05:41.308 --> 05:43.842
Well, I'm not
like that anymore.

05:43.844 --> 05:47.379
James, I understand
this is difficult to hear.

05:47.381 --> 05:49.948
No, you don't
understand, Dad!

05:49.950 --> 05:51.283
You got to be king!

05:56.056 --> 05:57.889
[James] Not how
the law's written!

05:57.891 --> 06:00.058
Well, this is what I think
of that law!

06:00.060 --> 06:00.959
Hyuh!

06:00.961 --> 06:03.061
-Take that, law!
-[Sofia] James?

06:03.063 --> 06:04.496
Are you okay?

06:04.498 --> 06:07.332
Sofia, I just went
from being the future king

06:07.334 --> 06:08.867
to the future nothing,

06:08.869 --> 06:11.737
so, no,
I'm not feeling so great.

06:11.739 --> 06:15.040
I'm so sorry. I can't imagine
how that must feel.

06:15.042 --> 06:17.576
I spent my whole life
thinking I'd grow up

06:17.578 --> 06:19.578
to protect our kingdom
from bad guys,

06:19.580 --> 06:21.380
all that great king stuff!

06:21.382 --> 06:23.882
Well, that's not
all a king does.

06:23.884 --> 06:26.385
Now I'll never get
to protect the kingdom.

06:26.387 --> 06:28.887
Maybe you can just find
another way to do that

06:28.889 --> 06:31.022
without being king.

06:31.024 --> 06:34.092
Yeah, maybe I can.

06:34.094 --> 06:35.694
That's the spirit!

06:35.696 --> 06:37.429
I'll go work
on that right now!

06:37.431 --> 06:39.431
Okay, good luck!

06:39.433 --> 06:42.701
Oh, that was way easier
than I thought it would be.

06:42.703 --> 06:44.336
Sofia's right.

06:44.338 --> 06:47.005
I can protect
the kingdom

06:47.007 --> 06:49.040
by making sure
Enchancia doesn't get

06:49.042 --> 06:52.444
a selfish, self-centered queen
like Amber.

06:52.446 --> 06:55.380
Now, Princess Amber,
as heir to the throne,

06:55.382 --> 06:57.716
you have lots
of important wedding duties--

06:57.718 --> 06:59.918
greeting the guests,
presenting the cake...

06:59.920 --> 07:03.288
...and holding on
to Sir Bartleby's wedding ring
for safekeeping.

07:03.290 --> 07:06.691
It's one of a kind,
just like Sir Bartleby.

07:06.693 --> 07:09.728
I need you to keep it safe
until it's time for me

07:09.730 --> 07:11.797
to give it to him
at the wedding ceremony.

07:11.799 --> 07:16.201
Ah! I'll guard this
with all of my future
queen abilities.

07:21.975 --> 07:24.543
I never thought
this day would come,

07:24.545 --> 07:29.247
but now that it has,
it just feels so right!

07:29.249 --> 07:33.785
¶ I've always loved
being a princess ¶

07:33.787 --> 07:35.954
¶ The gowns,
the balls ¶

07:35.956 --> 07:38.657
¶ The jewels galore ¶

07:38.659 --> 07:41.226
¶ But I started to wonder ¶

07:41.228 --> 07:46.131
¶ What else life
has in store ¶

07:46.133 --> 07:51.169
¶ And now I see
there's something more ¶

07:51.171 --> 07:53.138
¶ I will be queen ¶

07:53.140 --> 07:55.340
¶ That's the path for me ¶

07:55.342 --> 07:57.776
¶ I've always known
deep down ¶

07:57.778 --> 08:00.011
¶ That it was
meant to be ¶

08:00.013 --> 08:02.447
¶ Enchancia's queen ¶

08:02.449 --> 08:04.816
¶ It is clear to see ¶

08:04.818 --> 08:08.453
¶ That I was born
to rule ¶

08:08.455 --> 08:12.324
¶ Yes, it was meant to be ¶

08:13.260 --> 08:15.827
¶ I have so much ¶

08:15.829 --> 08:18.096
¶ I know I could offer ¶

08:18.098 --> 08:20.298
¶ I'll help the folks ¶

08:20.300 --> 08:23.001
¶ Across our land ¶

08:23.003 --> 08:26.037
¶ And I can't wait
to tell them ¶

08:26.039 --> 08:30.175
¶ Everything
I've planned ¶

08:30.177 --> 08:35.313
¶ The future will be
so great and grand ¶

08:35.315 --> 08:37.315
¶ I will be queen ¶

08:37.317 --> 08:39.718
