¶ Yes, it was meant to be ¶

10:01.101 --> 10:02.567
Now remember,
Princess Amber,

10:02.569 --> 10:04.302
it's the heir
to the throne's job

10:04.304 --> 10:07.539
to greet wedding guests
in the custom
of their own land.

10:07.541 --> 10:10.208
Yes, Baileywick. Ahem!

10:12.145 --> 10:13.278
[laughing]

10:13.280 --> 10:15.313
I've been practicing
these for weeks!

10:15.315 --> 10:18.483
They're really hard,
and there's no way Amber
will know them all.

10:18.485 --> 10:22.854
Introducing the King and Queen
of Trufflandia!

10:24.491 --> 10:27.459
[both]<i> Bon jour monsieur!</i>
<i> Faisons la fete!</i>

10:28.762 --> 10:31.262
Okay, she made
a lucky guess.

10:31.264 --> 10:34.265
Sooner or later,
her luck will run out.

10:34.267 --> 10:36.134
Royals from Freezenberg?

10:36.136 --> 10:40.138
Their Majesties, the King
and Princess of Freezenberg!

10:40.140 --> 10:43.041
[all shivering]

10:44.111 --> 10:45.143
Too easy.

10:45.145 --> 10:46.444
[James] Mermaids?

10:46.446 --> 10:49.314
Her Royal Highness
of Merroway Cove,

10:49.316 --> 10:50.482
Queen Emmeline!

10:50.484 --> 10:51.816
[horse neighs]

10:55.255 --> 10:57.122
Nah, she
already knows that one.

10:57.124 --> 10:58.490
What are you doing?

10:58.492 --> 11:01.159
Making sure everyone sees
that Amber doesn't deserve

11:01.161 --> 11:02.961
to be the heir to the throne.

11:02.963 --> 11:04.429
James, you can't do that!

11:04.431 --> 11:08.299
Oh, yeah?
Watch me.

11:08.301 --> 11:11.970
Gnomes? Hmm. I could never
remember their greeting!

11:11.972 --> 11:13.171
Perfect!

11:14.374 --> 11:17.709
Uh, please follow me,
King, uh...

11:17.711 --> 11:19.344
King Viridian!

11:19.346 --> 11:21.179
Hmm, yes, I knew that.

11:21.181 --> 11:22.947
You get
a front-of-the-line pass.

11:22.949 --> 11:24.315
Follow me, sir.

11:24.317 --> 11:26.718
I really don't think
this is a good idea.

11:26.720 --> 11:28.019
You're right, Sofia.

11:28.021 --> 11:29.320
I need to raise the bar

11:29.322 --> 11:31.523
and stump Amber
with some centaurs.

11:31.525 --> 11:35.960
Follow me, folks,
and you, too, giants.

11:35.962 --> 11:38.263
I didn't even know
giants had royals.

11:41.735 --> 11:44.335
Princess Amber,
these nice folks

11:44.337 --> 11:46.738
would like to receive
their royal greeting.

11:46.740 --> 11:48.206
Good luck.

11:48.208 --> 11:50.742
King Viridian
of the Gnomes!

11:50.744 --> 11:53.578
Please accept
my warmest welcome.

11:53.580 --> 11:58.116
[both yodeling]

12:01.421 --> 12:04.055
[speaks Gaelic]

12:04.057 --> 12:08.426
[laughs, speaks Gaelic]

12:08.428 --> 12:10.762
[heavy footfalls]

12:10.764 --> 12:14.232
Hail, hail!
My heart is open to you!

12:14.234 --> 12:16.334
[growly voice]
And mine to you.

12:17.337 --> 12:18.870
What? How did she know--?

12:18.872 --> 12:20.572
Come on, James,
you know she aced

12:20.574 --> 12:22.273
Majestic Formalities
at Royal Prep.

12:22.275 --> 12:24.409
But that was
the most boring class ever!

12:24.411 --> 12:27.779
Not for Amber.
She really loves
that boring stuff,

12:27.781 --> 12:29.781
and it's part of
being king or queen.

12:29.783 --> 12:33.418
Well, if I was king,
I could've learned to like it,

12:33.420 --> 12:36.521
but I guess that's never
gonna happen now.

12:36.523 --> 12:41.860
Princess Amber, you are
doing a fantastic job
representing the royals.

12:41.862 --> 12:42.894
Thank you,
Aunt Tilly!

12:42.896 --> 12:44.262
I've greeted
all the guests,

12:44.264 --> 12:45.396
presented the cake,

12:45.398 --> 12:48.299
and I still have your ring
safe and sound.

12:48.301 --> 12:52.203
Whiz-bang! Amber, you are going
to make a great queen.

12:52.205 --> 12:55.907
[sighs] I am so sick
of hearing people say that.

12:55.909 --> 12:58.276
Sofia!
There you are.

12:58.278 --> 13:01.112
I have another important task
for my maid of honor.

13:01.114 --> 13:02.614
Sure, Aunt Tilly.

13:02.616 --> 13:05.116
It's almost time
for the wedding ceremony.

13:05.118 --> 13:08.419
When I give the signal,
I'd like you to release

13:08.421 --> 13:10.655
this flock
of beautiful wedding...

13:10.657 --> 13:13.391
Doves? Oh, I love doves!

13:13.393 --> 13:16.261
Not doves, dear.
Doves are so ordinary.

13:16.263 --> 13:17.896
We're releasing...

13:18.899 --> 13:20.832
flying fish!

13:20.834 --> 13:25.637
Oh! Fish. That's a little...
unexpected.

13:25.639 --> 13:27.739
This could be my chance
to show everyone

13:27.741 --> 13:30.341
there's no way Amber
could make a good queen!

13:30.343 --> 13:33.144
Sofia, I'll need you to keep
a close eye on these critters.

13:33.146 --> 13:34.979
Keep them safe
in their little home,

13:34.981 --> 13:39.150
and when I give the signal,
let them soar into the sky!

13:39.152 --> 13:40.151
Got it!

13:40.153 --> 13:41.519
That sounds like

13:41.521 --> 13:43.421
a perfect job
for the heir to the throne!

13:43.423 --> 13:44.956
What are you talking
about, James?

13:44.958 --> 13:46.958
Aunt Tilly asked
Sofia to do it.

13:46.960 --> 13:50.495
Oh, I'm sorry, so you don't
think you can handle it?

13:50.497 --> 13:53.498
Of course I can
handle it! [scoffs]

13:53.500 --> 13:57.168
I would be honored to take care
of your fish, Aunt Tilly.

13:57.170 --> 13:58.703
That's fine with me.

13:58.705 --> 14:02.106
Okay! Then I'm sure
their fins are in good hands.

14:02.108 --> 14:04.275
Duchess Tilly?
May I have a moment?

14:04.277 --> 14:06.344
Ooh! It's almost time.

14:06.346 --> 14:09.781
Meet us by the ceremony tent
in a few minutes.

14:09.783 --> 14:13.284
I'm glad to see you've
come around to the idea
of Amber being queen.

14:13.286 --> 14:14.986
Oh, y-yeah,
I'm over that.

14:14.988 --> 14:18.489
Hey, isn't that
your wombeast friend?

14:18.491 --> 14:20.859
It is!
Hi, Wilbur!

14:21.995 --> 14:24.696
Uh-oh. Amber,
your tiara is crooked!

14:24.698 --> 14:26.197
Oh! Dear.

14:28.201 --> 14:31.002
Hi, little guys?
Who wants to get out early?

14:31.004 --> 14:32.570
[gasps] You all do?

14:32.572 --> 14:33.905
Okay!

14:33.907 --> 14:35.640
[laughing]

14:37.210 --> 14:38.643
Amber, the fish!

14:39.713 --> 14:40.812
Oh, no!

14:42.983 --> 14:45.650
Pardon me!
I'm terribly sorry.

14:45.652 --> 14:47.185
Come back, fish!

14:47.187 --> 14:49.754
As your future queen,
I command you to--

14:49.756 --> 14:51.656
-[gasps]
-Oh, no!

14:51.658 --> 14:55.026
[blubbers]
Oh, my hair!

14:55.028 --> 14:58.196
Princess Amber,
the king of the Kobalds!

14:58.198 --> 14:59.764
You touched his hair!

14:59.766 --> 15:04.769
Oh, Your Majesty,
I'm so, so sorry.

15:04.771 --> 15:08.273
I'll help fix it
once I get the fish.

15:08.275 --> 15:11.609
Wow! Princess Amber
sure messed that up!

15:11.611 --> 15:13.711
Prince James
to the rescue!

15:13.713 --> 15:15.713
[Amber struggling]

15:15.715 --> 15:18.416
Careful, Amber, you might
get your dress dirty!

15:18.418 --> 15:19.784
Oh, it doesn't matter!

15:19.786 --> 15:21.519
I'm doing this
for Aunt Tilly!

15:21.521 --> 15:22.687
Oh! Gotcha!

15:25.458 --> 15:28.593
Wow, Amber doesn't care
if her dress gets dirty?

15:28.595 --> 15:30.028
That's right.

15:30.030 --> 15:32.397
She's not the pampered princess
she used to be!

15:32.399 --> 15:33.464
Is that all of them?

15:33.466 --> 15:35.300
No! I see more!

15:35.302 --> 15:38.603
Here, little fishies! Ha!

15:38.605 --> 15:40.071
[gasps]

15:40.073 --> 15:41.472
The wedding ring!

15:45.478 --> 15:47.111
No!

15:50.216 --> 15:51.616
It's gone!

15:51.618 --> 15:53.618
Oh, this is a disaster!

15:53.620 --> 15:55.486
I didn't mean for that
to happen.

15:55.488 --> 15:58.656
The day started off
so well,

15:58.658 --> 16:01.492
but then I messed
everything up!

16:01.494 --> 16:03.294
I let Aunt Tilly's
fish get out,

16:03.296 --> 16:06.097
and I touched
the Kobald king's hair!

16:06.099 --> 16:08.399
And then Aunt Tilly's ring!

16:08.401 --> 16:10.301
I lost it!

16:10.303 --> 16:12.270
You're being too hard
on yourself, Amber.

16:12.272 --> 16:14.772
Yeah, I mean, this may not
be<i> all</i> your fault.

16:14.774 --> 16:16.607
Of course it is!

16:16.609 --> 16:18.509
Look at all the damage
I caused

16:18.511 --> 16:21.412
in just a few hours
as heir to the throne!

16:21.414 --> 16:23.414
I'd probably destroy
the whole kingdom

16:23.416 --> 16:26.084
if I ever became queen,
which is why...

16:26.086 --> 16:27.685
[sighs] I won't!

16:27.687 --> 16:31.356
I'm not the right person
to rule Enchancia.

16:31.358 --> 16:32.490
What are you saying?

16:32.492 --> 16:33.491
He is.

16:33.493 --> 16:34.525
You don't mean--

16:34.527 --> 16:35.693
I do.

16:35.695 --> 16:37.595
If Aunt Tilly
gave up the throne,

16:37.597 --> 16:38.529
so can I.

16:38.531 --> 16:40.164
James can be king.

16:40.166 --> 16:43.368
From now on,
you're heir to the throne.

16:43.370 --> 16:44.535
I quit.

16:44.537 --> 16:45.636
Amber, wait.

16:45.638 --> 16:48.272
Young royals,
you're needed right away.

16:48.274 --> 16:50.775
The ceremony
is about to begin.

16:50.777 --> 16:52.543
Might as well tell
everyone the news,

16:52.545 --> 16:56.547
and tell Aunt Tilly
that I've lost
her special ring.

16:58.551 --> 16:59.684
Aren't you coming?

16:59.686 --> 17:02.520
You need to take over
the heir-to-the-throne duties.

17:02.522 --> 17:03.621
I guess.

17:03.623 --> 17:05.123
James, what's wrong?

17:06.693 --> 17:08.292
You're going to be king!

17:08.294 --> 17:09.627
Isn't that what you wanted?

17:09.629 --> 17:11.996
I thought so,
but now...

17:11.998 --> 17:13.364
What is it?

17:13.366 --> 17:15.233
I have to tell you
something, Sofia.

17:15.235 --> 17:18.970
I'm the reason Amber
messed things up.

17:18.972 --> 17:21.372
I let the flying fish
out of their home.

17:21.374 --> 17:23.174
James, how could you!

17:23.176 --> 17:25.810
I know, I don't deserve
to be king,

17:25.812 --> 17:28.046
and Amber does deserve
to be queen.

17:28.048 --> 17:29.680
You have to tell her!

17:29.682 --> 17:31.182
You have
to make things right!

17:31.184 --> 17:32.850
But even if I tell her,

17:32.852 --> 17:34.852
I've still lost
Aunt Tilly's ring.

17:34.854 --> 17:36.654
[fish fussing]

17:36.656 --> 17:39.357
-[gasps] There it is!
-Let's get it!

17:39.359 --> 17:42.160
You still have that magic
wing-giving thingy, right?

17:42.162 --> 17:44.996
The Whenever Wings wand? Yes.

17:44.998 --> 17:46.230
Brilliant!

17:46.232 --> 17:48.366
Wait, James, Tilly said
not to use it.

17:48.368 --> 17:49.734
<i> Flutterous featherus!</i>

17:50.603 --> 17:52.036
<i> Flutterous featherus!</i>

17:52.038 --> 17:53.204
What are you doing?

17:53.206 --> 17:54.605
Trying to give
the ring wings

17:54.607 --> 17:56.574
so it'll fly up
out of the water.

17:56.576 --> 17:57.909
<i> Flutterous featherus!</i>

17:57.911 --> 18:00.011
Agh, but it
won't stay still!

18:00.013 --> 18:01.913
<i> Flutterous featherus!</i>

18:01.915 --> 18:04.348
Ah... don't worry.
I'll get it.

18:04.350 --> 18:06.084
Or you might hit
something else!

18:06.086 --> 18:08.586
-I think you should stop--
-I did it!

18:10.223 --> 18:11.789
<i> Flutterous terminus!</i>

18:11.791 --> 18:14.692
[Baileywick]
Children, please, the ceremony!

18:14.694 --> 18:16.627
We've got to get
this to Amber!

18:16.629 --> 18:18.763
Before she tells everyone
she won't be queen!

18:18.765 --> 18:20.298
Let's go!

18:26.739 --> 18:27.705
[James] Amber, no!

18:27.707 --> 18:30.408
-We have the ring!
-You do?

18:30.410 --> 18:32.443
And you're still
the heir to the throne!

18:32.445 --> 18:33.511
I am?

18:35.815 --> 18:36.914
[growls]

18:36.916 --> 18:39.317
[gasps] Oh, no!

18:39.319 --> 18:41.252
What in the kingdom
is that?!

18:41.254 --> 18:43.254
[gasps] It's a kondraki!

18:43.256 --> 18:45.756
Wait, kondrakis
don't have wings!

18:45.758 --> 18:47.658
Well, this one does.

18:47.660 --> 18:48.893
[screaming]

18:48.895 --> 18:52.163
Everyone, take cover
under the tables!

18:52.165 --> 18:54.532
[centaur speaking Gaelic]

18:56.636 --> 18:59.103
Where did that thing
come from?

18:59.105 --> 19:01.739
James, I think you gave
that kondraki wings

19:01.741 --> 19:03.307
with the Whenever Wings wand.

19:03.309 --> 19:05.676
I know, Sofia. We've got
to change it back!

19:05.678 --> 19:07.178
<i>Flutterous terminus!</i>

19:07.180 --> 19:09.747
<i> Flutterous terminus!</i>

19:09.749 --> 19:12.116
Oh, he's too far away
and moving too fast!

19:12.118 --> 19:13.351
What do we do?

19:13.353 --> 19:14.485
We need a plan.

19:14.487 --> 19:15.786
Don't look at me!

19:15.788 --> 19:17.955
I was a disaster
as the future leader.

19:17.957 --> 19:20.324
You weren't
a disaster, Amber.

19:20.326 --> 19:21.425
You were great!

19:21.427 --> 19:22.960
Oh, what are you
talking about?

19:22.962 --> 19:24.529
I messed everything up!

19:24.531 --> 19:26.697
[sighs] Only because I set
the fish loose

19:26.699 --> 19:28.766
and did everything else
I could think of

19:28.768 --> 19:30.101
to make things
harder for you.

19:30.103 --> 19:31.469
You what?

19:31.471 --> 19:35.039
I'm really,
really sorry, Amber.

19:35.041 --> 19:37.675
I thought you
shouldn't be queen,

19:37.677 --> 19:39.877
but now I see
you're great at it.

19:39.879 --> 19:42.313
You even like doing
the boring stuff.

19:42.315 --> 19:44.382
So I didn't really
mess things up?

19:44.384 --> 19:46.617
No, you were amazing.

19:46.619 --> 19:48.486
Thank you, Sofia.

19:48.488 --> 19:50.688
Okay, people, we have
a kondraki to stop

19:50.690 --> 19:51.789
and a wedding to save.

19:51.791 --> 19:53.791
Sofia, I need you
to find Aunt Tilly

19:53.793 --> 19:55.960
and Sir Bartleby and make sure
they're all right.

19:55.962 --> 19:58.462
-Okay.
-I'll help keep
the wedding guests safe.

19:58.464 --> 20:00.665
And James-- ugh.

20:00.667 --> 20:01.832
I know
what he can do!

20:01.834 --> 20:02.900
[whispers]

20:02.902 --> 20:05.336
Oh! Yes!

20:05.338 --> 20:09.040
James, we could really use
your knight skills.

20:09.042 --> 20:10.107
Got it!

20:12.245 --> 20:13.511
Are you two okay?

20:13.513 --> 20:14.845
Oh, we're fine, Sofia,

20:14.847 --> 20:17.515
but I don't remember
inviting a kondraki.

20:17.517 --> 20:18.883
[Sofia] What does he
even want!?

20:18.885 --> 20:24.188
[growling] Ugh, cake! Cake!

20:24.190 --> 20:26.891
Cake? He's just after
some cake?

20:26.893 --> 20:28.726
Most kondrakis
do have a sweet tooth.

20:28.728 --> 20:30.828
Ugh! I've got
to tell Amber!

20:30.830 --> 20:32.496
[speaking Gaelic]

20:32.498 --> 20:34.532
Amber! Amber!

20:34.534 --> 20:36.500
The kondraki!

20:36.502 --> 20:38.169
I think it's
after the wedding cake!

20:38.171 --> 20:40.438
Guard, go protect the cake!

20:43.343 --> 20:45.710
Cake! Cake!

20:45.712 --> 20:47.945
Guards! Cut a slice of cake,

20:47.947 --> 20:50.948
and we can use some
to lure him away.

20:50.950 --> 20:52.283
But just one piece,

20:52.285 --> 20:55.686
because dessert is really
for the invited guests.

20:55.688 --> 20:57.255
-[kondraki growling]
-James!

20:57.257 --> 21:00.391
See if you can get him
to follow you away
from the wedding!

21:00.393 --> 21:03.294
Hey, kondraki!
You want cake?

21:03.296 --> 21:05.796
I got cake for ya!

21:05.798 --> 21:07.898
Ugh! I can't get
his attention!

21:07.900 --> 21:09.533
I need to get closer!

21:09.535 --> 21:11.035
<i> Flutterous featherus!</i>

21:12.238 --> 21:14.605
Whoa, brilliant!

21:14.607 --> 21:15.773
Go get him, James!

21:18.311 --> 21:20.778
Yoo-hoo! You want
some cake?

21:20.780 --> 21:22.213
Follow me!

21:22.215 --> 21:23.681
Go, James, go!

21:32.158 --> 21:34.659
It's all yours, kondraki!

21:35.595 --> 21:37.028
<i> Flutterous terminus!</i>

21:43.803 --> 21:45.336
You did it, Sofia!

21:45.338 --> 21:46.437
We all did it!

21:46.439 --> 21:48.773
<i> Flutterous terminus!</i>

21:48.775 --> 21:50.641
[Roland] Sofia! James!

21:50.643 --> 21:52.310
That was fantastic!

21:52.312 --> 21:55.946
You were braver
than the bravest knight!

21:55.948 --> 21:57.848
You protected us all.

21:57.850 --> 22:00.751
James, you said you wanted
to protect the kingdom

22:00.753 --> 22:03.154
without doing any
of the boring king stuff.

22:03.156 --> 22:04.789
Why don't you be a knight?

22:04.791 --> 22:07.124
Yeah, maybe you're right!

22:07.126 --> 22:10.695
Actually, I think
that's all I've ever
really wanted to be!

22:10.697 --> 22:13.998
Enchancia will be lucky
to have such a brave defender.

22:14.000 --> 22:17.868
In fact, my first act as queen

22:17.870 --> 22:22.506
is to declare you
First Knight of the Realm!

22:22.508 --> 22:24.308
That's very sweet,

22:24.310 --> 22:27.945
but, Amber, I'm afraid
you cannot do that.

22:27.947 --> 22:30.314
Not until you are
officially queen.

22:30.316 --> 22:33.818
Oh! Well,
then when I become queen,

22:33.820 --> 22:35.686
it will be
my first act.

22:35.688 --> 22:38.122
Um, guys? As Tilly's
maid of honor,

22:38.124 --> 22:40.191
I should
probably remind you

22:40.193 --> 22:42.526
we need to make sure
she gets married today!

22:42.528 --> 22:44.695
-That's true.
-Whoops!

22:45.798 --> 22:47.998
And do you, Duchess Matilda,

22:48.000 --> 22:50.868
take Sir Bartleby
to be your husband?

22:50.870 --> 22:53.003
I do.

22:53.005 --> 22:55.072
Then, by the power
vested in me

22:55.074 --> 22:57.408
by King Roland
of Enchancia,

22:57.410 --> 23:00.878
I now pronounce you
husband and wife!

23:00.880 --> 23:02.813
Or as we like
to call you,

23:02.815 --> 23:05.149
adventurer and knight!

23:05.151 --> 23:06.584
Huzzah, Tilly.

23:06.586 --> 23:08.319
[crying] Oh...

23:08.321 --> 23:12.323
-And I said I wouldn't cry!
-Yay!

23:12.325 --> 23:15.559
-[whispers]
-Now? Uh, okay!

23:15.561 --> 23:17.561
<i> Flutterous featherus!</i>

23:17.563 --> 23:19.563
<i> Flutterous featherus!</i>

23:21.234 --> 23:22.900
[crowd] Whoa!

23:22.902 --> 23:24.702
[applause]

23:24.704 --> 23:26.904
<i> Flutterous featherus!</i>

23:26.906 --> 23:28.606
<i>Flutterous featherus!</i>

23:31.043 --> 23:33.611
<i> Flutterous featherus!</i>

23:35.081 --> 23:37.748
